customrecordcustomfield.help: The actual transactional response code from Authorize.Net
customrecordcustomfield.label: Response Code

customrecordcustomfield.help: The error code number is this type
customrecordcustomfield.label: Response Code Type

customrecordcustomfield.help: If there was an error - the error code should be recorded here for additional details
customrecordcustomfield.label: Error Code

customrecordcustomfield.help: Authorize.net Integration Advice - based on response code (data may not populate if Authorize.net provides no advice)
customrecordcustomfield.label: Integration Advice

customrecordcustomfield.help: The internal id or the primary key for external transaction that was used in the request - this is important only to know information about the request and is not critical.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Request Transaction ID

customrecordcustomfield.help: The Authorize.Net transaction identifier - this is used to capture, settle, refund, this is the transaction key for future calls.
customrecordcustomfield.label: Transaction ID

customrecordcustomfield.help: If checked this is a call for CIM management and does not impact the status of the transaction for auth/capture/settle purposes
customrecordcustomfield.label: CIM Call

customrecordcustomfield.help: Anthorize.Net specific alphanumeric message code used for explicit error reporting
customrecordcustomfield.label: Message Code
